===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#A [[sister]] of someone's [[parent]]
#A [[sister-in-law]] of someone's parent-or the live partner of a father's brother.
#Your grandparent's sister or brother's wife (also known as a great aunt or grandaunt).
#A grandmother. (usually called ''auntie'') 
#An affectionate term to call a woman of an older generation than you, by means of [[fictive kin]].
#{{vulgar}} (''cant'') Mine aunt; a bawd or procuress: a title of eminence for the senior dells, who serve for instructresses, midwives, &c. for the [[dell]]s.

